cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with image segmentation. Additionally, the use of deep learning networks and the evaluation on real-world image datasets further supports this categorization. The paper also involves memory-efficient techniques, which could potentially fall under the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of collaborative networks and the focus on accuracy-memory usage trade-offs suggest that the paper could also be categorized under machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM). Finally, the potential use of neural networks for segmentation could also place the paper under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
